{
  "text": "The present study shows that NNHL is mostly comprised B-cell disease, as in K. Lei findings [CITATION_1] . In a study of 54 patients with nasopharyngeal lymphomas, Ye et al. found an equal incidence of B-cell (51%) and T-cell (49%) lymphomas in the nasopharynx [CITATION_2] . Similarly, in the recent study of 113 patients reported by Cheung et al. [CITATION_3] , lymphoma involving the nasal cavity was mostly of NK/T-cell or T-cell lineage, while almost half of the lymphomas involving the nasopharynx were of B-cell lineage.",
  "citation_candidates": [
